THE TERRITORY’S authorities have used live rounds, pepper spray and water cannon with blue dye to mark participants in ever-growing protests. What else might they resort to? The Baltic states, worried about Russian expansionism, are countering the old-school spycraft of the Kremlin’s agents. And, drag acts sashay into the mainstream. Runtime: 21 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn